================================================================================
AI MODEL LICENSES
================================================================================

LocalMind is designed to work with locally-hosted language models via Ollama.
The AI models themselves are NOT part of this software and are subject to
their own license agreements. Below are common models and their licenses:

  - Gemma (Google):       Gemma Terms of Use
                          https://ai.google.dev/gemma/terms

  - Llama (Meta):         Meta Llama Community License
                          https://llama.meta.com/llama3/license/

  - Mistral:              Apache License 2.0
                          https://mistral.ai

  - Phi (Microsoft):      MIT License
                          https://huggingface.co/microsoft/phi-2

  - Qwen (Alibaba):       Tongyi Qianwen License
                          https://huggingface.co/Qwen

  - DeepSeek:             MIT License / DeepSeek License
                          https://huggingface.co/deepseek-ai

Users are solely responsible for reviewing, understanding, and complying
with the license terms of any AI model they download and use with LocalMind.


================================================================================
WEB SPEECH API
================================================================================

The voice input (Speech Recognition) and voice output (Speech Synthesis)
features use the Web Speech API, which is a browser-native capability.
No third-party software is bundled for these features. Speech recognition
may route audio through the browser vendor's cloud services (e.g., Google
for Chrome). Users should review their browser's privacy policy.


